post_text:
The Fort Totten School Board election on June 16, 2020 will be held by mail-in ballot only. You must complete an absentee/mail ballot application form and either return by mail, email, or drop in black box at the front door of the Alternative/CTE building. Drop box will be available from 8am – 3pm (most days). Once I’ve received that form, a ballot will be mailed to you, at the address indicated on the application, for completion. Return your ballot by mail or place in the drop box at the front of the Alternative/CTE building. Ballots must be in my possession by 5pm on June 15th. No ballots will be accepted on election day. Please call me at 701-766-1427 or 701-732-0425 if you have any questions.

To request an absentee/mail ballot application form:

*Download from the link provided below

*Request by phone: 701-766-1427 or 701-732-0425

*Request by email: megan.weisser@k12.nd.us

*Remember to mark the School Election box when completing your request.

https://5il.co/fxtq

Megan Weisser, Business Manager

Fort Totten Public School

post_text:
Congratulations to the GBB team on their 1st place District finish last night.

Grades are due today @ 9:00 AM.

Leadership meeting after school every Wednesday in Mrs. Benz's room.

Weight Lifting will be available on Monday and Wednesday from 3:30 - 4:30 in the weight room. Starting date 2ill be 2/19.

Students - Make sure to get to class on time. 3 Tardies/week = Lunch Detention, 4+ Tardies/week = 1 day of ISS. Fifteen total tardies = 1 day of ISS. After 91 class period absences students will be dropped.

Concession Workers (If you cannot make it, you will need to find someone to fill in for you):

Saturday - Christina Anderson, AJ Benz, Stacy Benz, Maddy, Destri, Mena, Shallan, & Hope

After School Tutoring will be available Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday's after school in Ms. Marte's Room. Tutoring will be available until 5:30. A transport bus will be available at that time. Please arrive to tutoring by 3:45.

Menu
Tuesday - Chicken Hotdish
Wednesday - Sub Sandwiches
Thursday - Tater Tot Hotdish
Friday - Chili

Athletics:
Tuesday - BBB @ Warwick
Saturday - BBB vs. Shiloh

Students with attendance issues can make up attendance time during the after school tutoring times on a minute to minute basis.

After School Tutoring will be available Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday's after school in Ms. Marte's Room. Tutoring will be available until 5:30. A transport bus will be available at that time. Please arrive to tutoring by 3:45.

Scholarship opportunity for Seniors through NDTC. Go to https://www.gondtc.com//scholarships.php for more information.

Scholarship opportunity for students enrolling in a land grant tribal college (like CCCC) in the areas of ag, food, natural resources, or related. Please see Mrs. Black for more information.

Friday - Meatloaf Dinner
